1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,879
What's wrong with that? Why can't it work in American English?

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:11,679
But our people, our relatives, the Syrians, practice this.

3
00:00:12,419 --> 00:00:18,760
Literally, you know, in Damascus when they hang, up to now in Damascus, during my father's time,

4
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:27,339
when a man is hung, they actually write his record on a big piece and they hang it on his neck.

5
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:29,480
Up to now,

6
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:31,039
and during my father's time,

7
00:00:31,039 --> 00:00:32,560
the plaque on his neck was hung,

8
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:34,219
and they wrote on it,

9
00:00:34,219 --> 00:00:37,299
and put a big plaque around his neck,

10
00:00:37,299 --> 00:00:38,740
his whole record,

11
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:41,200
not for him to read but for others to read,

12
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,880
and they hang it.

13
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:44,659
They actually hang it on his neck.

14
00:00:44,659 --> 00:00:46,920
And they hang it up to now.

15
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:48,000
As a matter of fact,

16
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,899
during my father's time, we saw it.

17
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:52,420
So that's what

18
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:53,899
the 'Ta'iruhu fi 'unuqihi' is.

19
00:00:53,899 --> 00:00:56,640
They take it literally.

20
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:57,359
LITERALLY!

21
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:00,380
Like you said.

22
00:01:04,199 --> 00:01:07,299
Can you think of an idiom, an American idiom?

23
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:07,799
Idiom?

24
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:10,200
What was it, "hit the nail on the head"?

25
00:01:10,579 --> 00:01:13,040
Oh, I think you want to answer this one.

26
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:13,420
Idiom.

27
00:01:15,119 --> 00:01:16,239
Which one?

28
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:16,920
Idiom?

29
00:01:17,340 --> 00:01:23,939
Or something like that.

30
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,040
And then we have, for example,

31
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:38,780
"given his record behind his back."

32
00:01:39,799 --> 00:01:41,500
like "raining cats and dogs."

33
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,180
It doesn't really rain cats and dogs.

34
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:45,359
But you do get the record behind your back

35
00:01:45,359 --> 00:01:47,319
if you have a bad record.

36
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,920
Oh yeah.

37
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:06,159
The reality is everybody will be in Hell,

38
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:07,359
initially,

39
00:02:08,119 --> 00:02:09,860
because God will not be there.

40
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:12,240
In the absence of God...

41
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:12,800
the absence of God is Hell.

42
00:02:14,919 --> 00:02:22,860
So, then God comes and becomes Heaven for the believers and becomes a worse Hell for

43
00:02:22,860 --> 00:02:23,379
the disbelievers.

44
00:02:26,039 --> 00:02:26,879
Yeah.

45
00:02:26,879 --> 00:02:26,939
Yeah.

46
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:29,560
Right.

47
00:02:36,199 --> 00:02:39,780
You don't have to prove it, prove it, prove it.

48
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:40,740
Oh, everybody is.

49
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:43,520
Even Jesus, and Muhammad, and Moses.

50
00:02:47,460 --> 00:02:48,020
Yeah.

51
00:02:49,479 --> 00:02:50,039
Everybody.

52
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:52,900
Everybody is in Hell first.

53
00:02:58,020 --> 00:03:02,879
It is not a pun. It is actually...

54
00:03:02,879 --> 00:03:07,599
Let me explain this point a little bit. We are told...

55
00:03:07,599 --> 00:03:19,960
We are told that this initial Hell will serve to make you appreciate Him.

56
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:26,979
because you will not appreciate the good thing unless you know what the bad thing is like.

57
00:03:34,259 --> 00:03:38,500
But you see, Hell is not what they picture to you, the fire and the flames for you.

58
00:03:40,039 --> 00:03:45,120
The terrible fate, but the terrible thing about it is eternity and hopelessness.

59
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:50,020
So that initial Hell is not eternal, and it is not hopeless.

60
00:03:51,420 --> 00:03:54,639
That's why Arik and I were suggesting to stay two years.

61
00:03:54,939 --> 00:03:55,939
What would you say?

62
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:56,919
We'll pass through now.

63
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:57,599
We'll pass.

64
00:03:57,699 --> 00:03:58,500
No, I won't stay.

65
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,379
We'll pass by it.

66
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,860
Go to see some things, and stay?

67
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:02,479
Exactly.

68
00:04:02,479 --> 00:04:04,199
You know, or work from that place.

69
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:05,539
We'll be transients.

70
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:06,780
Like we are.

71
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,620
Just a transient camp, instead of...

72
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:24,420
May I just mention something? May I mention something in the famous Nicene Creed, which was written in the Council of Nicaea.

73
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:28,920
It says that, talking about Jesus Christ as part of the belief,

74
00:04:30,339 --> 00:04:37,899
Then He descended into Hell, and then ascended into Heaven. It's very fancy.

75
00:04:38,139 --> 00:04:39,040
What is this one?

76
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:44,360
The Apostles' Creed, I think. That's the one that has how he...

77
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:51,339
Jesus Christ and so and so, then He descended into Hell, and then He ascended into Heaven.

78
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:56,899
Which is very, very parallel. It's really close to that.

79
00:04:57,540 --> 00:05:00,839
You can see that verse.

80
00:05:02,419 --> 00:05:03,139
Yes.

81
00:05:03,879 --> 00:05:04,439
Yes.

82
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:08,980
71.

83
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:11,120
Yes.

84
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:14,779
So, initially we all go in.

85
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,939
Every single one

86
00:05:16,939 --> 00:05:18,480
of you will initially enter

87
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,379
therein.

88
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,800
This is an inevitable matter decreed by the

89
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:23,079
Lord.

90
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:26,720
It is written in a most powerful

91
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:27,540
word in Arabic.

92
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,160
Hatman. Inevitable.

93
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,339
Maqdiyyan. A manifest decree by God.

94
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,560
Some will be taken out.

95
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,480
I remember.

96
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:44,740
We have to read the next verse,

97
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:45,399
72.

98
00:05:45,399 --> 00:05:48,740
Then we save those who work righteousness.

99
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:50,339
And we leave the wicked.

100
00:05:50,339 --> 00:05:51,680
They will be humiliated.

101
00:05:58,339 --> 00:06:00,620
it only makes sense because

102
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:02,759
the sequence of events in the Hereafter

103
00:06:02,759 --> 00:06:04,879
is that you will be resurrected first.

104
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:09,079
Now when you are resurrected

105
00:06:09,079 --> 00:06:10,939
and God is not there physically,

106
00:06:10,939 --> 00:06:12,879
then God comes

107
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:13,279
differently.

108
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,740
So the period of absence

109
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:18,560
of God's physical presence

110
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,759
is Hell.

111
00:06:25,059 --> 00:06:32,779
The Purgatory will be for people who didn't make it to Heaven and didn't make it to Hell.

112
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:39,040
People who said La ilaha illallah like a year and a half before they died.

113
00:06:40,339 --> 00:06:42,000
They didn't get the chance to grow.

114
00:06:43,019 --> 00:06:43,500
No.

115
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,180
It's fame-seeking.

116
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:46,500
It's hypocritical.

117
00:06:47,219 --> 00:06:49,160
No, hypocrites will be the fuel of Hell.

118
00:06:49,220 --> 00:06:50,740
Hypocrisy is not a factor.

119
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:54,060
And there is no revision of that.

120
00:06:54,939 --> 00:06:55,540
Insha'Allah.

121
00:06:55,699 --> 00:06:56,860
But not one of them is there.

122
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:03,420
But those people are, according to the Quran, they have powers of discernment because they

123
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:04,319
know they can recognize.

124
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:06,279
They know who are the ones.

125
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,860
Yeah, everybody recognizes everybody.

126
00:07:09,199 --> 00:07:10,680
No, no, I'm talking about this particular one.

127
00:07:10,759 --> 00:07:11,399
The Purgatory.

128
00:07:11,519 --> 00:07:11,860
The Purgatory.

129
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:15,699
On the A'raf, they know by the marks of certain people,

130
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:19,879
they can tell who are frustrated, and they know the others by their marks,

131
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,779
So they are people of discernment.

132
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:24,240
I don't know if that's the word that you use,

133
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:26,439
there are people who have discernment.

134
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:33,220
Everybody will recognize everybody, by the way, by their look.

135
00:07:37,239 --> 00:07:39,420
I don't know if you can tell.

136
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:42,639
I'm aware of the flow, but,

137
00:07:42,779 --> 00:07:44,319
I don't know if you can tell.

138
00:07:47,239 --> 00:07:49,540
It depends on where you're from,

139
00:07:49,699 --> 00:07:53,439
and if you have a hill

140
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:56,259
or a hill itself that goes down there,

141
00:07:56,379 --> 00:07:58,240
it's going to go straight down.

142
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:13,180
they will sneak into Heaven.

143
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:15,180
but they will suffer even worse

144
00:08:15,180 --> 00:08:17,180
from the presence of God.

145
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:20,699
The baby soul

146
00:08:20,699 --> 00:08:23,199
suffers more in the presence of God

147
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:25,139
in Heaven.

148
00:08:25,139 --> 00:08:27,500
So when they sneak up to Heaven

149
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,819
and become closer to God, they cannot stand it.

150
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:33,840
They shatter, and they go back, voluntarily, they go back to Hell.

151
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,559
The nearness to God is so bright, so they sneak back again.

152
00:08:37,779 --> 00:08:39,600
They will spend an eternity in this way.

153
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:45,679
They keep hoping that maybe when they come closer to God,

154
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:48,159
they will be able to stand it, but they can't, and they go back.

155
00:08:49,180 --> 00:08:51,259
So it breaks the monotony for them.

156
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:10,980
They will spend an eternity circulating between hell and a worse hell, which is heaven. That sounds

157
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:11,980
ironic, isn't it?

158
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:21,799
So that's why when the time comes, the people whose souls have grown will enjoy being in heaven

159
00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:22,340
automatically.

160
00:09:22,340 --> 00:09:28,860
And the ones whose souls were shrunken and small, they suffer terribly.

161
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:37,399
It was worse than hell. Worse than hell. And the proof is that they prefer to go on and

162
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:38,460
go back to hell.

163
00:09:43,420 --> 00:09:45,580
No one could argue with the fact of it.

164
00:10:04,139 --> 00:10:13,559
Yes, Abdullah, we'll come to you.

165
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:21,940
You're also Abdullah, aren't you?

166
00:10:23,399 --> 00:10:24,279
We're all Abdullah.

167
00:10:46,540 --> 00:10:52,139
When all of them combine against you and your plan, you should realize that you are on the right way.

168
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:01,440
I guess the main idea here is

169
00:11:04,540 --> 00:11:15,799
that every believer is in some kind of a trial, or is shunned.

170
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:30,500
Because the thing is, we have to live with the one truth.

171
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:45,039
And the thing is, we should know that, you know, maybe we are not going to see one another again.

172
00:11:52,019 --> 00:12:01,899
He was a great believer, despite that, he was still... so, I didn't think that, you know, he...

173
00:12:01,899 --> 00:12:21,659
And, um, the others too, well, I didn't get to know them, but, uh, and he was, he made some kind of good, and he just... he just did. Uh, well, the rest of us were on it, you know, all the time.

174
00:12:21,659 --> 00:12:38,820
But I'm sure that every believer will have some kind of miracle in their life, just for themselves, to build their belief.

175
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,659
Just as it was in the past.

176
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:50,980
In the past, they used to have those outward works.

177
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:53,019
We used to see for ourselves.

178
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,580
We used to see for ourselves.

179
00:12:55,860 --> 00:12:56,600
We used to see for ourselves.

180
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:06,320
It can be a miracle that is perceived by everybody in this community, you know,

181
00:13:06,399 --> 00:13:09,759
it can be a sign of hope or something.

182
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:11,980
It can be a sign or a miracle.

183
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,700
It can be a sign of hope.

184
00:13:16,220 --> 00:13:19,940
Or it can be a spiritual thing.

185
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:23,820
Not necessarily a divine sign here,

186
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:31,679
but it could be something that... it could be a miracle for the person.

187
00:13:31,679 --> 00:13:43,059
I got a letter from a graduate school in New York City, I got a letter from...

188
00:14:03,699 --> 00:14:07,039
The question here was, "Do you not believe?"

189
00:14:08,399 --> 00:14:11,600
Of course, Abraham does believe.

190
00:14:12,379 --> 00:14:14,120
But he wanted his heart to be at ease.

191
00:14:15,299 --> 00:14:19,480
We had a very good example of that growth here.

192
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,659
We were very fortunate

193
00:14:23,659 --> 00:14:27,720
when we had the unique, great fortune

194
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:32,320
of having the miracle of the Quran come out of this mosque

195
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:36,960
in the whole world, proving that every word

196
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,600
of this Quran is from God.

197
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:44,679
A very, very unique, great,

198
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:47,639
very humbling discovery, and we are...

199
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:52,679
we didn't realize how great it was in this mosque, but

200
00:14:52,679 --> 00:14:57,320
I guess we do now. We do realize how great it is.

201
00:14:57,320 --> 00:15:04,019
But, I'm sure each one of you met people who say, when we believe the Quran is from God, we don't need this.

202
00:15:06,259 --> 00:15:09,879
So now what they're saying, we are better than Abraham, we don't need the reassurance.

203
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:16,860
We did believe in the Quran from God before the discovery of this miracle in the Quran.

204
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:22,899
But when we saw it, our faith was strengthened greatly.

205
00:15:22,899 --> 00:15:29,379
In Sura 74 and Sura 98, God says this is to strengthen the faith of the believers.

206
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:33,120
Our faith was strengthened.

207
00:15:35,899 --> 00:15:43,600
So this example here of Abraham asking and needing reassurance, means that sincere

208
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:50,279
believers need reassurance, and require reassurance.

209
00:15:50,279 --> 00:15:52,259
But there was nothing wrong with it.

210
00:15:53,139 --> 00:15:56,379
Also the bird miracle was an actual incident

211
00:15:56,379 --> 00:16:01,039
where Abraham took four birds

212
00:16:01,039 --> 00:16:05,159
and studied the markings on the birds.

213
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,360
And then he cut the birds in pieces

214
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:12,059
and put one piece on the top of each hill.

215
00:16:13,379 --> 00:16:14,519
Far, far apart.

216
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,940
And when he called them,

217
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:19,620
God actually put the birds together.

218
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:30,820
The same principle applies to the martyrs; of course God has the angels do that,

219
00:16:30,919 --> 00:16:35,299
He doesn't have to do it Himself; it's all done by His command.

220
00:16:36,340 --> 00:16:45,240
So this is an actual incident, showing resurrection of the dead, and the verse before this too.

221
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:49,480
Remember the one God resurrected from death after 100 years.

222
00:16:54,379 --> 00:16:56,600
The belief in resurrection is very important.

223
00:16:59,759 --> 00:17:03,080
It is required along with belief in God.

224
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:18,140
So, we're going to quit now, but I want to remind you that, as we will see throughout

225
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:22,279
the verses of the Quran, it is very important that we develop our soul and let it grow.

226
00:17:24,539 --> 00:17:29,799
The more your soul grows, the higher is your rank for eternity.

227
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:42,740
And one of the most intensive worships that make you grow, is the dhikr at dawn.

228
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:51,119
It's really a shame to sleep through it, when there's a shift change going on right at this time,

229
00:17:51,799 --> 00:18:03,220
between night and day. So don't sleep through it. It is a blessing. It's not a terrible chore, you know, to just

230
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:08,279
wake up and come to the Masjid at 6 o'clock in the morning. It's a very pleasant thing.

231
00:18:08,279 --> 00:18:20,460
We are going to institute that. The commemoration in a group is also very effective, because

232
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:29,559
when one person in the group next to you is uplifted, all of us feel it.

233
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:39,420
Also, there will be a little change to the program. We used to study Arabic after the Fajr prayer.

234
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:48,299
But the point was made that after the Fajr prayer we are very high

235
00:18:48,299 --> 00:18:51,240
and the Arabic lessons are really a let-down.

236
00:18:52,099 --> 00:18:56,380
It's like crashing down from very high.

237
00:18:56,460 --> 00:18:58,460
So we're going to move the Arabic language lessons

238
00:18:58,460 --> 00:19:01,160
to before the Quranic study and lecture.

239
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,680
So the people who want to study Arabic will come.

240
00:19:05,859 --> 00:19:07,539
This is not

241
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,299
to say that studying Arabic is inferior to being a Quranic student.

242
00:19:11,740 --> 00:19:13,480
Tomorrow there will be no Arabic lessons,

243
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:16,519
as Rukhansa has a full day at work.

244
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:17,160
Mm-hmm.
